{"type":"message","id":"219906c7","parentId":"7a363e93","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:11:37.379Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is replying to my previous message and seems confused about what I said. They're asking \"What do you mean what was sent?\"\n\nLooking at my previous message, I said \"Both messages sent.\" - but I didn't actually send any messages in that previous turn. I was reporting what happened in a checkpoint update (ID 11).\n\nThe user seems confused because I said \"both messages sent\" but they might not have asked me to send any messages, or they're wondering what messages I'm referring to.\n\nLet me clarify - I was just reporting the status of an automated email monitoring job. The \"messages sent\" likely refers to notifications that were sent as part of the checkpoint job, not messages I composed and sent on purpose.\n\nI should clarify what I meant without being confusing.\n","thinkingSignature":"d597992dd83c76c4449dbdf8e251bfb59fb0bdf3c543a6c9fbf2129eb6b21400"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nSorry for the confusion! I was reporting the results of an automated email checkpoint job that's running hourly. The \"both messages sent\" refers to notifications that went out as part of that automated process — not me manually sending you anything.\n\nBasically: the hourly email check completed and it reported that two notification messages were sent (likely to you or to another agent). The checkpoint was updated to ID 11.\n\nWere you asking me about something specific, or were you just confused by that phrasing?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26841,"output":255,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27288,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777479077389,"responseId":"064160a557099116f2f6efc8528e16f9"}}
