{"type":"message","id":"2d9b74fb","parentId":"c0cbb867","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:14:25.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby is showing me the repeated iCloud email notifications he's getting. It looks like the same emails from RC Leasing are being reported over and over - specifically ones about:\n1. Looking for a new apartment (multiple emails)\n2. Pay stubs and bank statements being requested\n\nThe issue seems to be that the checkpoint system isn't marking these as \"seen\" or processed, so they're being reported every time the email check runs. Each time it reports them as \"new\" even though they've already been reported.\n\nI should look at the email checkpoint script to understand how it's tracking what's been reported. Let me find it.","thinkingSignature":"ae63c973989997483951b4d91bbe590762ab04934df17f4f34306b7cea5d0fa5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2omtrjw5o7uj_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~ -path \"*/SecondBrain*\" -name \"*.py\" 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":24752,"output":171,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25179,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777479259524,"responseId":"0641615bc4d22d60bf8695b3c58b450f"}}
