{"type":"message","id":"21a2ba22","parentId":"51886454","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:14:42.530Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is seeing repeated iCloud email notifications for the same RC Leasing emails. The email check script seems to be checking the same emails and reporting them as \"new\" every time, when they're actually old emails that have already been seen. \n\nThis is a state/tracking issue — the email checkpoint script isn't properly tracking which emails have already been reported. I need to find the email check script and fix the checkpoint tracking logic so it doesn't keep re-reporting the same old emails.\n","thinkingSignature":"1c8a224f5d781cfb4e06a25a81d4382b68871c8e3ecaca2fde67245743cb341d"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI see — you're getting the same RC Leasing emails reported over and over. The issue is that the email checkpoint script isn't properly tracking which emails have already been seen, so it keeps re-reporting old emails as \"new\" every time it runs.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_93qv3t0smtkc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/Desktop/SecondBrain -name \"*.py\" 2>/dev/null | grep -i email","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":73,"output":205,"cacheRead":25088,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25366,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777479277391,"responseId":"0641616d90d3b4d53e895d625002af5e"}}
