{"type":"message","id":"8eefa82f","parentId":"f5feb590","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:15:09.883Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'm not finding a separate iCloud email check script. Looking at the messages Bobby referenced - they say \"iCloud\" but the script only uses Gmail. Let me think about what might be happening:\n\n1. There's a \"last_icloud_id.txt\" file with \"11\" in it\n2. There's a \"new_emails_found.json\" with old emails from April 5\n\nLooking at the messages Bobby shared - they're from Taylor Alexander (RC Leasing) about apartment stuff. These are from iCloud email. But I don't see an iCloud email check script.\n\nWait - maybe there's ANOTHER agent or cron job that handles iCloud emails? Or maybe the checkpoint job I mentioned sends both Gmail AND iCloud emails in one message?\n \nSo when I mentioned \"Gmail has 1 new (PetScreening)\" and \"iCloud has 6 new (all apartment application related)\" - that suggests a checkpoint system that's pulling from both accounts. My smart_email_check.py only handles Gmail though, so there's either another script checking iCloud, or the checkpoint job itself is aggregating both sources.\n\nThe last_icloud_id.txt file shows \"11\" as the checkpoint ID, and the new_emails_found.json contains test data from early April that doesn't match the RC Leasing emails Bobby is actually seeing. This means either those messages are from a different system entirely, or the checkpoint job is pulling email data separately from the Gmail script.\n","thinkingSignature":"232c06aa0c0d37b7c2136d627a30dfd899a0e82b7d9492c5019f8554fa943b51"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yryvhnd3zium_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~ -maxdepth 8 -type f \\( -name \"*.py\" -o -name \"*.sh\" \\) 2>/dev/null | xargs grep -l -i \"icloud\\|imap\" 2>/dev/null | head -10","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":487,"output":377,"cache