ich uses `newer_than:1h`, iCloud just lists all envelopes every time with no date filter — and there's no checkpoint to remember what's already been sent. Let me\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/memory/dreaming/light/2026-04-29.md:- Candidate: Assistant: Got it — the iCloud check has no \"already seen\" tracking. Let me fix it properly now.\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/memory/dreaming/light/2026-04-29.md:- Candidate: Assistant: The iCloud check has no state tracking at all — it re-reports everything every time. The fix: save a timestamp after each run and only show emails newer than that on the next run.\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/memory/dreaming/light/2026-04-29.md:- Candidate: Assistant: Now I understand the full picture. The cron job (`449f0d3e-002d-4362-b785-e56c0682c27b`) runs `himalaya envelope list --account icloud` with **no date filter** — it lists everything, every time, with no memory of what's been reported. The fix: track the last-seen iClou\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/memory/dreaming/light/2026-04-29.md:- Candidate: Assistant: Now let me update the cron job with proper iCloud deduplication:\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/memory/dreaming/light/2026-04-29.md:- Candidate: Assistant: Done. Here's what was wrong and what I fixed: **The problem:** The iCloud check ran `himalaya envelope list --account icloud` with **no filter at all** — every time it fired, it listed all iCloud emails from scratch. There was no checkpoint to remember what you'd alrea\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/memory/dreaming/light/2026-04-29.md:- Candidate: Assistant: 📬 ICLOUD — New Mail (1 new) 🟡 IMPORTANT: • RC Leasing — Re: Looking for new apartment └ Amy from Royal Cove is asking for bank statements to complete your application ⚠️\n/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/memory/dreaming/light/2026-04-29.md:- Candidate: Assistant: No new iCloud emails (last seen ID is 11, newe