{"type":"message","id":"a08f192a","parentId":"2470dc80","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:15:36.199Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the issue. Looking at the dreaming memory, there's a clear pattern:\n\n1. The iCloud email check was running WITHOUT a checkpoint/since-filter\n2. The last seen ID is stored in `last_icloud_id.txt` (currently shows \"11\")\n3. The problem was that the iCloud check wasn't properly filtering to only show NEW emails since the last run\n\nFrom the dreaming memory, it looks like someone (Dean or a previous session) was supposed to have fixed this. Let me check the current state of the iCloud email check cron.\n\nActually, looking at the last entry in the dreaming memory: \"📬 **GMAIL** — No new emails (last 1 hour) 📬 **ICLOUD** — No new emails (last checkpoint: ID 11)\" - this suggests the last checkpoint was ID 11.\n\n\nBut when I look at the current `last_icloud_id.txt`, it shows \"11\" - so either the fix was only partially implemented or the checkpoint logic isn't working as intended. The original message mentions \"all messages are at or below the last tracked ID of 11\", which makes sense if the newest emails have IDs 6-11 and the last seen ID is also 11, meaning there genuinely aren't new emails to report.\n\nHowever, I'm realizing the core issue here: Bobby's seeing the same emails repeatedly in Telegram, which means the iCloud check script doesn't have proper deduplication logic built in. The \"last seen ID 11\" checkpoint exists, but if new emails arrive with IDs 1-5, they'd still get reported even though they've been seen before. The real problem is likely that the email check is re-sending the same content without properly filtering out what's already been reported.\n","thinkingSignature":"61f3df8815282d14125cf535cbd62b285e9864998004b98561d9457ac203278c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI found the issue. The iCloud email check isn't properly filtering — it's re-reporting the same emails every time because there's no working checkpoint that tracks what was already sent.\n\nLet me check the current iCloud email check script:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mxfjbylytu2b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/skills/himalaya/SKILL.md 2>/dev/null | head -100"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1514,"output":454,"cacheRead":28800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30768,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777479323050,"responseId":"0641619b1cb4c06103436a825c5e0d4e"}}
