{"type":"message","id":"16f7f714","parentId":"fe960a41","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:16:01.273Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, it's printing 6 total but then failing on `m['from'][:40]`. The error says `KeyError: slice(None, 40, None)` which means `m['from']` isn't a string. But the repr shows the keys... Wait, `repr(m['from'][:40])` would try to subscript the result of `m['from'][:40]`, not `m['from']`. Actually the error is `KeyError: slice(None, 40, None)`. That's a weird key error - it means something is trying to access a dict with a slice key `[40]`. This happens when `m['from']` is itself a dict and we're trying to do `m['from'][:40]`. Let me check what `m['from']` actually is.","thinkingSignature":"71452f0b2a97f43776cd801f7b164fe69fa1d306988f3d56024ff69b66a02ec4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1mc9tq3bj2v9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"himalaya envelope list --account icloud --output json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; msgs=json.load(sys.stdin); print(json.dumps(msgs[0], indent=2))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":210,"output":241,"cacheRead":32128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32579,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777479357178,"responseId":"064161bda70b6c53fa469467212bcf20"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6bdda831","parentId":"16f7f714","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:16:03.048Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1mc9tq3bj2v9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"11\",\n  \"flags\": [\n    \"Answered\",\n    \"Seen\"\n  ],\n  \"subject\": \"Re: Looking for new apartment\",\n  \"from\": {\n    \"name\": \"RC Leasing\",\n    \"addr\": \"RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com\"\n  },\n  \"to\": {\n    \"name\": \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\",\n    \"addr\": \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\"\n  },\n  \"date\": \"2026-04-28 15:03+00:00\",\n  \"has_attachment\": false\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1757,"aggregated":"{\n  \"id\": \"11\",\n  \"flags\": [\n    \"Answered\",\n    \"Seen\"\n  ],\n  \"subject\": \"Re: Looking for new apartment\",\n  \"from\": {\n    \"name\": \"RC Leasing\",\n    \"addr\": \"RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com\"\n  },\n  \"to\": {\n    \"name\": \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\",\n    \"addr\": \"rtg.bobby@icloud.com\"\n  },\n  \"date\": \"2026-04-28 15:03+00:00\",\n  \"has_attachment\": false\n}","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777479363047}}
{"type":"message","id":"88c0bbe0","parentId":"6bdda831","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:16:07.617Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the structure. The `from` field is an object with `name` and `addr`. Let me check all 6 messages and understand the issue.\n\nThe issue is that the `from` field is an object `{\"name\": \"...\", \"addr\": \"...\"}`, not a string. So when the code does `m['from'][:40]`, it fails because you can't slice a dict.\n\nBut looking at the messages Bobby was shown, it seems like the report was going out. So maybe the issue isn't that the code crashes - maybe the issue is that it's re-reporting the same emails every time because the checkpoint tracking isn't working properly.\n\n\nLet me trace through the memory to see what's actually happening with the iCloud email fetching and checkpoint system.","thinkingSignature":"ac4e5003a42107bbf42f4eec18ba7de5a486dd4e7d0d91720115671db0917faa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_cl4xgnpb00yp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"himalaya envelope list --account icloud --output json 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nmsgs=json.load(sys.stdin)\nprint(f'Total: {len(msgs)}')\nfor m in msgs:\n    print(f\\\"ID {m['id']} | {m['from']['name'][:30]} | {m['subject'][:45]} | {m['date']}\\\")\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":228,"output":272,"cacheRead":32320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32820,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777479363050,"responseId":"064161c3a38cc2d3d551008212f2b41b"}}
