{"type":"message","id":"6f4b6cdb","parentId":"40e2e676","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:16:38.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the issue clearly. Bobby is seeing the same 6 iCloud emails every single time the cron job runs. The last seen ID was saved as 11, but all 6 emails (IDs 6-11) are being reported as \"new\" every time. The issue is that the checkpoint comparison is broken - it's not properly filtering out already-seen emails.\n\nThe problem: when I save \"last_icloud_id.txt\" as 11, and then next time I run and get IDs 6-11, I need to only show emails with ID > 11. But since 11 is the HIGHEST ID in the current list (newest), and we're comparing as integers, none of them are > 11. So it should correctly say \"no new emails.\" But Bobby is still seeing all 6 emails being reported.\n \nLooking at the memory entries, I can see what's actually happening: when the last seen ID is 11 and the newest email is also 11, it's correctly identifying there are no new emails. But then there are entries showing the assistant is actively scanning and reporting on these same emails - like it's fetching the email list and then sending summaries of what's there, even when nothing new has arrived.\n\nThe pattern is clear: the first run reports the emails as new, but subsequent runs should say \"no new emails since last check\" once the ID hasn't changed. Yet I'm seeing the same emails being listed multiple times, which suggests the checkpoint isn't actually preventing re-scanning of the same messages. I need to trace through where this filtering breaks down - it looks like the code might be running the full envelope list every time instead of actually checking against what was already reported.\n","thinkingSignature":"a6b43d69830c1175c7254ce71f872655282aa7ddaefd4741fe6a71716f7573cf"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nFound it. The iCloud check is re-reporting the same emails every time instead of tracking what's already been sent. Let me fix the checkpoint logic now.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_upftwqj3k0xr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_id.txt 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_email_summary.txt 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":325,"output":445,"cacheRead":32544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":33314,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777479368681,"responseId":"064161c8e1d04288d9a2e19049e48c5e"}}
