{"type":"message","id":"4b5a92cd","parentId":"ef8a7b1a","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:17:48.946Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_6qe78cy74e6d_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"type\":\"thinking_level_change\",\"id\":\"5d45634d\",\"parentId\":\"f50dd507\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:37.163Z\",\"thinkingLevel\":\"off\"}\n{\"type\":\"custom\",\"customType\":\"model-snapshot\",\"data\":{\"timestamp\":1777475377175,\"provider\":\"minimax-portal\",\"modelApi\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"modelId\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\"},\"id\":\"7aa82bba\",\"parentId\":\"5d45634d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:37.175Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"3306382c\",\"parentId\":\"7aa82bba\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:37.181Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"[cron:449f0d3e-002d-4362-b785-e56c0682c27b Emmy Email Check (Gmail + iCloud)] Check emails in BOTH Gmail AND iCloud and send TWO SEPARATE messages back-to-back.\\n\\n=== MESSAGE 1: GMAIL ===\\nSTEP 1 - Run: gog gmail search 'in:inbox newer_than:1h' --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com\\n\\nSTEP 2 - Classify emails as:\\n- URGENT (bills, payments, security alerts)\\n- IMPORTANT (jobs, appointments, personal)\\n- LOW PRIORITY (promotions, newsletters)\\n\\nSTEP 3 - Send FIRST message to 8212808444 with format:\\n\n GMAIL \n New Mail (X new)\\n\\n\n--\n [1-line summary]\\n\\nIf NO new Gmail emails: '\n GMAIL \n No new emails'\\n\\n=== MESSAGE 2: ICLOUD (with deduplication) ===\\nSTEP 4 - Read last seen ID: cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_id.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"0\\\"\\n\\nSTEP 5 - List iCloud emails (newest first): himalaya envelope list --account icloud 'order by date desc' 2>&1 | grep -v WARN\\n\\nSTEP 6 - For each email where ID > last_seen_ID:\\n  - Read it: himalaya message read <id> --account icloud\\n  - Note its content for reporting\\n\\nSTEP 7 - Send SECOND message to 8212808444 with format:\\n\n ICLOUD \n New Mail (Y new)\\n\\n\n URGENT:\\n\n--\n [Sender] \n [Subject]\\n  \n [1-line summary]\\n\\nIf NO new iCloud emails: '\n ICLOUD \n No new emails'\\n\\nSTEP 8 - After sending, update checkpoint: echo <highest_new_id> > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_id.txt\\n\\nRULES:\\n- Send the Gmail message FIRST, then the iCloud message immediately after\\n- Only include sections that have emails (skip empty categories)\\n- Keep summaries to 1 line\\n- Mark action needed with \n\\n- ICLOUD: Only report emails with ID strictly greater than the saved last_icloud_id\\nCurrent time: Wednesday, April 29th, 2026 - 11:09 AM (America/New_York) / 2026-04-29 15:09 UTC\\n\\nUse the message tool if you need to notify the user directly for the current chat. If you do not send directly, your final plain-text reply will be delivered automatically.\"}],\"timestamp\":1777475377179}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"82818571\",\"parentId\":\"3306382c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:42.321Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me follow the cron job instructions. I need to:\\n1. Check Gmail first\\n2. Send the Gmail results\\n3. Then check iCloud with deduplication\\n4. Send the iCloud results\\n\\nLet me start by checking Gmail.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"74d258bc91692395366413e4214c4051edb043f0b2e6a38ef06002d7688884da\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_ynbxxle7e8pa_1\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"gog gmail search 'in:inbox newer_than:1h' --max 50 --account rtg.bobby@gmail.com 2>&1\"}},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_ynbxxle7e8pa_2\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_id.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"0\\\"\"}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax-portal\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":148,\"output\":146,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":21052,\"totalTokens\":21346,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"d15be73c\",\"parentId\":\"82818571\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:43.558Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_ynbxxle7e8pa_1\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ID                DATE              FROM                                        SUBJECT                                         LABELS                            THREAD\\n19dd9b57160d56ac  2026-04-29 10:41  YSL Beauty <noreply@email.yslbeautyus.com>  Personalize Your Gift In Time for Mother\ns Day  CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS,UNREAD,INBOX  -\"}],\"details\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"exitCode\":0,\"durationMs\":1218,\"aggregated\":\"ID                DATE              FROM                                        SUBJECT                                         LABELS                            THREAD\\n19dd9b57160d56ac  2026-04-29 10:41  YSL Beauty <noreply@email.yslbeautyus.com>  Personalize Your Gift In Time for Mother\ns Day  CATEGORY_PROMOTIONS,UNREAD,INBOX  -\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777475383558}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"324bd56e\",\"parentId\":\"d15be73c\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:43.559Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_ynbxxle7e8pa_2\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"11\"}],\"details\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"exitCode\":0,\"durationMs\":21,\"aggregated\":\"11\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777475383558}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"1388cd70\",\"parentId\":\"324bd56e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:47.513Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"So we have:\\n- Gmail: 1 new email from YSL Beauty about Mother's Day promotion (LOW PRIORITY)\\n- Last iCloud ID: 0\\n\\nLet me now check iCloud emails.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"60ead98bf40c85fe4b03ba775d12901f592cf6557037b41969b336ef2ef2b399\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_1pfv6kdnww7q_1\",\"name\":\"exec\",\"arguments\":{\"command\":\"himalaya envelope list --account icloud 'order by date desc' 2>&1 | grep -v WARN | head -20\"}}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax-portal\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":1042,\"output\":94,\"cacheRead\":20401,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":21537,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1777475383561,\"responseId\":\"06415237d442618e57539b5012c238bd\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"915a508e\",\"parentId\":\"1388cd70\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:48.932Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_1pfv6kdnww7q_1\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"| ID | FLAGS | SUBJECT                                 | FROM             | DATE                   |\\n|----|-------|-----------------------------------------|------------------|------------------------|\\n| 6  |    R  | Re: Apartment Inquiry (Around mid June) | Taylor Alexander | 2026-01-22 10:31-05:00 |\\n| 7  |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-13 15:46+00:00 |\\n| 8  | !  R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-27 12:20+00:00 |\\n| 9  |       | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-27 19:06+00:00 |\\n| 10 |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-28 12:40+00:00 |\\n| 11 |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-28\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"59126076\",\"parentId\":\"915a508e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:57.835Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Now I have the iCloud emails. The last_icloud_id is 0, so all emails with ID > 0 should be reported (IDs 6-11).\\n\\nWait, let me re-read the instructions. The last_icloud_id.txt returned \\\"0\\\" so all emails with ID strictly greater than 0 should be reported. That means IDs 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11.\\n\\nBut wait - some of these might be old (from January and February). The instruction says \\\"newer_than:1h\\\" for Gmail, but for iCloud it doesn't specify a time filter - it just says ID > last_seen_ID. Let me check the emails to understand their content.\\n\\nActually, let me re-read the cron message more carefully. It says:\\n- \\\"For each email where ID > last_seen_ID\\\" - so all IDs greater than 0\\n- \\\"Only report emails with ID strictly greater than the saved last_icloud_id\\\"\\n\\nSo all 6 emails (6-11) are new compared to last_icloud_id=0.\\n\\nLet me read eac\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"1b7be0ee\",\"parentId\":\"59126076\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:59.200Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_3y2vzveu22su_1\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"From: Taylor Alexander <taylora.hubrealty@gmail.com>\\nTo: Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\\nSubject: Re: Apartment Inquiry (Around mid June)\\n\\nHello!\\n\\nWe do only hold apartments for 6 weeks, so it is fairly early to discuss\\navailability for June as I am not really sure what we would have at that\\ntime.\\nYou would want to follow up with me about mid April so I can discuss more\\naccurate availability with you.\\n\\nAt this very moment, I only have 2 bedrooms available. This can change\\nbefore June, and we will hopefully have some one bedrooms as well.\\nOur 2 bedrooms are renting for $2265 and our 1 bedrooms at $1865, both\\noptions including heat and hot water.\\n\\nPlease keep my information and touch base with me as we get closer.\\nI'd love to work something out and help you get settle\nPM Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com> wrote:\\n\\n> Hello,\\n>\\n> I am interested in relocating to the area in June. I will need to\\n> determine the exact dates between my current lease and my move from\\n> Tennessee. I understand that this is relatively early in the year, but I am\\n> currently researching the areas. I am originally from Wappingers, and one\\n> of my close friends resides in the community and has only positive things\\n> to say about it. I would love to see if there are any available options.\\n>\\n> Thank you,\\n> Robert Galletta\\n>\\n>\\n\\n-- \\nTaylor Alexander, Leasing Manager\\nRidgefield & Dutchess Apartments\\n845-454-2290\\n\\n\\n411 Meadow St.\\nFairfield, CT 06824\\n203-334-0181\\n\\nVisit our website\\nwww.hubrealty.com\\n\\nLike us on Facebook\\nRidgefield Apartments\\n<https://www.facebook.com/Ridgefieldapartmentspoughkeepsie>\\nDutchess Apartments\\n<https://www.facebook.com/DutchessApartmentsPoughkeepsie>\"}],\"details\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"exitCode\":0,\"durationMs\":1348,\"aggregated\":\"From: Taylor Ale\n--\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"e81a0bf4\",\"parentId\":\"2a04f295\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:10:08.331Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Now I have all the emails. Let me classify them:\\n\\n**GMAIL (1 new):**\\n- YSL Beauty \n Mother's Day promotion \n LOW PRIORITY\\n\\n**ICLOUD (6 new, IDs > 0):**\\n\\nLooking at the content:\\n- ID 6: Taylor Alexander (Hub Realty) \n old Jan 2026 inquiry about June apartment. This is IMPORTANT (personal/apartment hunting)\\n- ID 7: RC Leasing \n Apr 13 response with pricing/availability info. IMPORTANT\\n- ID 8: RC Leasing \n--\n ACTION NEEDED\\n- ID 11: RC Leasing \n Apr 28 asking for bank statements. IMPORTANT \n ACTION NEEDED\\n\\nAll the iCloud emails are from the same apartment hunting thread (Royal Cove). The most recent two (10 and 11) require action \n sending pay stubs and bank statements.\\n\\nLet me send the Gmail message first, then the iCloud message.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"9103f25b4fc59038f51ce88d8f9e45a4804aeda746d600ef463fcd951f628f0e\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_function_ucyf1gbrwmgx_1\",\"name\":\"message\",\"arguments\":{\"action\":\"send\",\"channel\":\"telegram\",\"target\":\"8212808444\",\"message\":\""}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777479468946}}
{"type":"message","id":"7511a9a6","parentId":"4b5a92cd","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:18:06.356Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture! Let me trace through what's happening:\n\n1. The cron job runs the **Email Check (Gmail + iCloud)** task\n2. It reads `last_icloud_id.txt` which returns `11`\n3. It then lists iCloud emails with `himalaya envelope list --account icloud 'order by date desc'`\n4. For each email where ID > last_seen_ID (i.e., ID > 11), it reads and reports them\n\nBut here's the problem:\n- The cron job says `last_icloud_id.txt` returned `11` \n\n\n- But that's actually the highest ID in the mailbox right now, not a timestamp from the last run\n- When the cron fires, it reads `11` as the last seen ID, then filters for IDs > `11` — which means **no new emails** since the highest ID is `11`\n- The issue is that `last_icloud_id.txt` was never updated after the previous run, so it's stuck at `11` even though new emails could have arrived since then\n\nLooking at the envelope list, all the emails are from the same thread about the apartment, and the user is seeing the same emails repeatedly because the checkpoint isn't advancing. Looking at the email dates from late April, all of these messages are actually quite recent—they span from April 13th through yesterday—so they're definitely being treated as new by the system. The real problem is that the checkpoint isn't advancing after each run, so the same emails keep getting reported as new when they shouldn't be.\n\nI need to trace through the cron job execution to see where the checkpoint update is failing. The session logs show the email check job is running, but I need to understand why the last seen ID isn't being saved properly between runs. I'm realizing the checkpoint system only advances forward—it saves the highest ID it's seen, so once ID 11 is recorded, it stays as the last checkpoint even if new emails arrive with lower IDs. The user's complaint about seeing the same emails repeatedly suggests either the cron job is re-sending the same report, or there's a separate issue with how emails are being tracked and displayed to the user.\n\nLooking at the session data from 11:09 AM, I can see the email check cron ran and reported 6 emails (IDs 6-11) as new when the last checkpoint was 0, but the user should only be seeing truly new emails if the checkpoint properly advances to 11 after that report. The problem might be that the checkpoint file isn't actually being updated after each run, or there's a timing issue where emails are arriving and being re-reported before the checkpoint can catch up. Let me check the current iCloud envelope list to confirm what's actually new since then.\n\nExamining the envelope data...\n\nI see the root cause now—the system isn't properly tracking which emails have already been reported, so it's sending the same messages repeatedly. The checkpoint should be advancing to ID 11 after each run, but something's preventing that from working correctly. I need to check the cron script to understand where the tracking mechanism is breaking down.\n","thinkingSignature":"dfc35133ee40ccc31d7f0253337f6357b5338b279e59dc2f990e7b7630564255"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nFound it! The iCloud check has a **checkpoint bug**. Here's what's happening:\n\n1. The cron runs and reads `last_icloud_id.txt` → gets `11`\n2. It lists all iCloud emails (IDs 6-11), but the filter is `ID > 11` → no matches\n3. So it should say \"No new iCloud emails\" and not send a report\n\n**But** — the message you replied to says it's showing those same 6 emails (RC Leasing thread) as \"new.\" That means the checkpoint is supposed to be at `0` so all 6 show as new, which means **the checkpoint file isn't being saved properly after each run.**\n\nLet me check the cron task definition:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_7hz7kbj5v0o7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron get 449f0d3e-002d-4362-b785-e56c0682c27b 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('message',{}).get('content', d.get('message','')))\" 2>/dev/null | head -80"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3446,"output":890,"cacheRead":41376,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45712,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777479468947,"responseId":"0641622de86ef415226e660b5e4aa30d"}}
