{"type":"message","id":"64b18a5b","parentId":"a41aad34","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:18:14.455Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me look at the actual cron message content more carefully from the session log. From what I can see in the session at 11:09 AM, the cron job had last_icloud_id.txt returning \"11\" (not \"0\"), but then when it listed the iCloud emails, they were IDs 6-11. So the condition `ID > last_seen_ID` would mean no emails would be reported (since 11 > 11 is false).\n\nBut the cron job was still sending the old emails. Let me check the actual current state of things. The issue Bobby is complaining about is that he's seeing the SAME emails reported over and over.\n\n\nLooking at the session from 11:09 AM, the last_icloud_id.txt file contained \"11\", yet the cron still reported IDs 6-11. This suggests the checkpoint tracking mechanism might not be functioning as intended—the file could have been stuck at \"11\" from a previous run, causing the system to incorrectly filter emails and resend them instead of advancing the checkpoint.\n","thinkingSignature":"d66f36e482d0c31bfb58a5118f451f7c6316d61a217049bf8d3e6460bd20bcf6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pzgha2zhowdb_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron get 449f0d3e-002d-4362-b785-e56c0682c27b 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":141,"output":267,"cacheRead":44800,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45208,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777479487302,"responseId":"0641623fabf7af88196605f0dff5c84e"}}
