tion_1pfv6kdnww7q_1\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"| ID | FLAGS | SUBJECT                                 | FROM             | DATE                   |\\n|----|-------|-----------------------------------------|------------------|------------------------|\\n| 6  |    R  | Re: Apartment Inquiry (Around mid June) | Taylor Alexander | 2026-01-22 10:31-05:00 |\\n| 7  |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-13 15:46+00:00 |\\n| 8  | !  R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-27 12:20+00:00 |\\n| 9  |       | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-27 19:06+00:00 |\\n| 10 |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-28 12:40+00:00 |\\n| 11 |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-28 15:03+00:00 |\"}],\"details\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"exitCode\":0,\"durationMs\":1410,\"aggregated\":\"| ID | FLAGS | SUBJECT                                 | FROM             | DATE                   |\\n|----|-------|-----------------------------------------|------------------|------------------------|\\n| 6  |    R  | Re: Apartment Inquiry (Around mid June) | Taylor Alexander | 2026-01-22 10:31-05:00 |\\n| 7  |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-13 15:46+00:00 |\\n| 8  | !  R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-27 12:20+00:00 |\\n| 9  |       | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-27 19:06+00:00 |\\n| 10 |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-28 12:40+00:00 |\\n| 11 |    R  | Re: Looking for new apartment           | RC Leasing       | 2026-04-28 15:03+00:00 |\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777475388931}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"1b7be0ee\",\"parentId\":\"59126076\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:59.200Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_3y2vzveu22su_1\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"From: Taylor Alexander <taylora.hubrealty@gmail.com>\\nTo: Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\\nSubject: Re: Apartment Inquiry (Around mid June)\\n\\nHello!\\n\\nWe do only hold apartments for 6 weeks, so it is fairly early to discuss\\navailability for June as I am not really sure what we would have at that\\ntime.\\nYou would want to follow up with me about mid April so I can discuss more\\naccurate availability with you.\\n\\nAt this very moment, I only have 2 bedrooms available. This can change\\nbefore June, and we will hopefully have some one bedrooms as well.\\nOur 2 bedrooms are renting for $2265 and our 1 bedrooms at $1865, both\\noptions including heat and hot water.\\n\\nPlease keep my information and touch base with me as we get closer.\\nI'd love to work something out and help you get settled in with our\\ncommunity.\\n\\nFeel free to reach out if you have any other questions or concerns.\\nThank you, look forward to hearing from you!\\n\\nOn Wed, Jan 21, 2026 at 6:13 PM Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com> wrote:\\n\\n> Hello,\\n>\\n> I am interested in relocating to the area in June. I will need to\\n> determine the exact dates between my current lease and my move from\\n> Tennessee. I understand that this is relatively early in the year, but I am\\n> currently researching the areas. I am originally from Wappingers, and one\\n> of my close friends resides in the community and has only positive things\\n> to say about it. I would love to see if there are any available options.\\n>\\n> Thank you,\\n> Robert Galletta\\n>\\n>\\n\\n-- \\nTaylor Alexander, Leasing Manager\\nRidgefield & Dutchess Apartments\\n845-454-2290\\n\\n\\n411 Meadow St.\\nFairfield, CT 06824\\n203-334-0181\\n\\nVisit our website\\nwww.hubrealty.com\\n\\nLike us on Facebook\\nRidgefield Apartments\\n<https://www.facebook.com/Ridgefieldapartmentspoughkeepsie>\\nDutchess Apartments\\n<https://www.facebook.com/DutchessApartmentsPoughkeepsie>\"}],\"details\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"exitCode\":0,\"durationMs\":1348,\"aggregated\":\"From: Taylor Alexander <taylora.hubrealty@gmail.com>\\nTo: Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\\nSubject: Re: Apartment Inquiry (Around mid June)\\n\\nHello!\\n\\nWe do only hold apartments for 6 weeks, so it is fairly early to discuss\\navailability for June as I am not really sure what we would have at that\\ntime.\\nYou would want to follow up with me about mid April so I can discuss more\\naccurate availability with you.\\n\\nAt this very moment, I only have 2 bedrooms available. This can change\\nbefore June, and we will hopefully have some one bedrooms as well.\\nOur 2 bedrooms are renting for $2265 and our 1 bedrooms at $1865, both\\noptions including heat and hot water.\\n\\nPlease keep my information and touch base with me as we get closer.\\nI'd love to work something out and help you get settled in with our\\ncommunity.\\n\\nFeel free to reach out if you have any other questions or concerns.\\nThank you, look forward to hearing from you!\\n\\nOn Wed, Jan 21, 2026 at 6:13 PM Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com> wrote:\\n\\n> Hello,\\n>\\n> I am interested in relocating to the area in June. I will need to\\n> determine the exact dates between my current lease and my move from\\n> Tennessee. I understand that this is relatively early in the year, but I am\\n> currently researching the areas. I am originally from Wappingers, and one\\n> of my close friends resides in the community and has only positive things\\n> to say about it. I would love to see if there are any available options.\\n>\\n> Thank you,\\n> Robert Galletta\\n>\\n>\\n\\n-- \\nTaylor Alexander, Leasing Manager\\nRidgefield & Dutchess Apartments\\n845-454-2290\\n\\n\\n411 Meadow St.\\nFairfield, CT 06824\\n203-334-0181\\n\\nVisit our website\\nwww.hubrealty.com\\n\\nLike us on Facebook\\nRidgefield Apartments\\n<https://www.facebook.com/Ridgefieldapartmentspoughkeepsie>\\nDutchess Apartments\\n<https://www.facebook.com/DutchessApartmentsPoughkeepsie>\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777475399199}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"98116d08\",\"parentId\":\"1b7be0ee\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:09:59.200Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_3y2vzveu22su_2\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"From: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\\nTo: Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\\n\\nThank you for your interest in Royal Cove! Offering affordable Apartments located in the Town of Poughkeepsie.\\nKindly Note: Availability is subject to change throughout the inquiry process.\\n1 Bedroom/ 1 Bath starting at $1825.00\\n2 Bedroom/ 1 Bath starting at $2150.00\\n3 Bedroom/ 1 Bath starting at $2595.00\\n\\nOnsite Amenities:\\nExterior amenities include a swimming pool, playground areas, picnic & grill areas, dog parks and basketball court. Interior amenities include laundry room on site, fully renovated  units, business center, lounge area and fitness center.\\nUtilities:\\nHeat ,Hot water, garbage, sewer, landscaping, etc. are included.  Electric, cable and internet are additional and paid for by tenants.\\nWhat you need to know before applying!\\nPet Friendly! One-time pet fee: $400 per dog & $200 per cat. Monthly Pet Rent is $35 per Dog & $25 per cat. No aggressive breeds (Rottweilers, Pit-Bulls, German Shepherds, Dobermans, Chows, etc.).  At full maturity they cannot weigh more than 50lbs. 2 pet maximum.\\nOur leases are for 1 year.\\n$20 application fee per adult (non-refundable).  All adults residing in the unit must be screened.  The screening process will consist of a credit check, background check, and mandatory pet screening .  You must provide your full social security number for the screening process.\\nTotal household NET income 2.5 times the monthly rent is required.    We look for a credit score of 600 or higher\\nRhino Partner- Rhino Policies start as low as $9 per month*, compared to an upfront cash deposit.\\nAs required per the lease agreement all new tenants will be enrolled in the Waiver Program at an additional $18 per month. Ask us how this program benefits you!\\nSpectrum through the property rep starting at $49.99 a month\\nPlease let us know if you have already applied to our sister properties: Royal Ledges Aor Royal Gardens\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n\\nAmy Smith\\n\\nLeasing Agent\\n\\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\\n\\nW | royalcoveapts.com<https://shared.outlook.inky.com/link?domain=royalcoveapts.com&t=h.eJx1jUEOwiAURK_SsLalvyjQrrwKhQ82YiGUGhvj3YWNO3cvmTczb7InT6aG3HKOE6UpHMrr8EQV89bp8CCnhtyr4PG1rC6HtY0pREz5aF0Ke6RJe1Rbya4_Jbpapb1AaSSCGJjl1poLH80ZJGih55kPQEGIXgLvGe-AyXEU9Q3r29_RaphirLv3BZeC8PkCt98_GQ.MEUCIQCWTK6waHQ5m4oXXmmk0HWUWuJpREFHCvC4dLlg9W3LSQIgBWmuktwnm5U9QNOCLRJfbL_fBqb8ylv8lngBFhSNwTY>\\n\\n\\n\\n[A picture containing text, font, screenshot, graphics  Description automatically generated]\\n\\n\\n\\nAmy Smith\\n\\nLeasing Agent\\n\\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\\n\\nW | royalcoveapts.com\\n\\n\\n\\n[A picture containing text, font, screenshot, graphics  Description automatically generated]\\n\\n\\n\\n________________________________\\nFrom: Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\\nSent: Monday, April 13, 2026 11:12 AM\\nTo: RC Leasing <rcleasing@lexingtonpg.com>\\nSubject: Looking for new apartment\\n\\n Hello, I hope you’re doing well. My partner Logan and I are currently searching for a 1-bedroom apartment and are looking to move in by early June, ideally before June 6. We are relocating from Tenn\\n[cid:inky-injection-inliner-03755809cc10337ec572b1f12a6beedf]\\nCaution: External (rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com>)\\nFirst-Time Sender   Details<removed-link>\\n[cid:inky-injection-inliner-97c0836b41e87f6018b00b7d2e96af51]\\n  Report This Email<removed-link>\\n\\n Hello,\\n\\n\\nI hope you’re doing well. My partner Logan and I are currently searching for a 1-bedroom apartment and are looking to move in by early June, ideally before June 6.\\n\\n\\nWe are relocating from Tennessee, and I do plan to come up in person to tour the apartment before moving.\\n\\n\\nWe do have a dog named Finnly who is about 50 lbs, so we would also like to know about your pet policies, \n\n⚠️ [... middle content omitted — showing head and tail ...]\n\nLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>> wrote:\\n\\n\\nGood Morning,\\n\\nOnce Logan completes his, I can run the apps. When are you looking to move by so I can make sure I will have one Available?\\n\\n\\nAmy Smith\\n\\nLeasing Agent\\n\\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\\n\\nW | royalcoveapts.com<https://shared.outlook.inky.com/link?domain=royalcoveapts.com&t=h.eJxNjssOgjAURH-FdC2Ulj6AFb_SllqJldtcipEY_1270LidM5MzT7JjJGNFLjmnkVKEw0QHd29S3hoHN3KqyLUUon8sa8iw1gkhecxHHRD2RNFFb7YPm36VFMqUCmWU00PfyfPQGmOtYMI7O3DueqasoUxr3fGWSd5IrgSTXdH5osMcGgvWHtPiIuzz98tc4F_0egOjEz3u.MEQCICsXyG_X4cTZgg-0e9IyTuzVOeNrMT8h6-k7gAqGLetIAiB4rEGZb0mixRUIMYoaWhCZfMtqFLiRhsLl1ogTXk3gFA>\\n\\n\\n\\n<Outlook-A picture .png>\\n\\n\\n\\n________________________________\\nFrom: rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com> <rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com>>\\nSent: Saturday, April 25, 2026 1:49 PM\\nTo: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>>\\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\\n\\n\\nHi Amy,\\n\\n\\n\\nI wanted to reach out to let you know that I have completed and submitted my portion of the rental application for Royal Cove. I am currently waiting on my partner, Logan, to finish his part of the application on his end.\\n\\n\\n\\nWe are still very interested in a 1 bedroom / 1 bathroom unit. Please let me know if you need anything else from me in the meantime, or if there are any updates on availability.\\n\\n\\n\\nThank you,\\n\\nRobert Galletta\\n<#part type=image/png filename=\\\"/Users/bobbygalletta/Downloads/Outlook-A picture .png\\\"><#/part>\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777475399201}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"d99f9be4\",\"parentId\":\"e81a0bf4\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:10:08.937Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_ucyf1gbrwmgx_1\",\"toolName\":\"message\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": true,\\n  \\\"messageId\\\": \\\"2045\\\",\\n  \\\"chatId\\\": \\\"8212808444\\\"\\n}\"}],\"details\":{\"ok\":true,\"messageId\":\"2045\",\"chatId\":\"8212808444\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777475408937}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"b17c60bd\",\"parentId\":\"c8bf824e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:10:16.131Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_edl3by4hrnmn_1\",\"toolName\":\"message\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"ok\\\": true,\\n  \\\"messageId\\\": \\\"2046\\\",\\n  \\\"chatId\\\": \\\"8212808444\\\"\\n}\"}],\"details\":{\"ok\":true,\"messageId\":\"2046\",\"chatId\":\"8212808444\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777475416131}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"5c713045\",\"parentId\":\"522e5aaa\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:10:19.031Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_function_3n8m2ze23jql_1\",\"toolName\":\"exec\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"(no output)\"}],\"details\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"exitCode\":0,\"durationMs\":21,\"aggregated\":\"\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy\"},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1777475419030}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"7b4e76da\",\"parentId\":\"5c713045\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T15:10:23.429Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"All done. I've sent both messages back-to-back as instructed. The Gmail message went first (1 promotion email), then the iCloud message (6 apartment-related emails with 2 requiring action).\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"9faf252a1fc71bfb4d8ac2cc5b3ca313d393aeb578a290938902f501dc91f8b1\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"📬 **GMAIL** — 1 new (Mother's Day promo) and **ICLOUD** — 6 new (apartment thread) messages sent. The iCloud checkpoint has been updated to ID 11.\\n\\nTwo iCloud emails from RC Leasing need action: pay stubs and bank statements weren't received properly.\"}],\"api\":\"anthropic-messages\",\"provider\":\"minimax-portal\",\"model\":\"MiniMax-M2.7\",\"usage\":{\"input\":8883,\"output\":109,\"cacheRead\":20401,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":29393,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1777475419032,\"responseId\":\"0641525b74845d1fd4deed63caaf0a4b\"}}[... 22496 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777479497321}}
{"type":"message","id":"2206f9a6","parentId":"d961894a","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:18:32.122Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see exactly what happened. At 11:09 AM (EDT) / 15:09 UTC on April 29, the cron job fired and ran. The problem was clear:\n\n1. The `last_icloud_id.txt` showed `0` (not `11`)\n2. So all emails with ID > 0 were reported as \"new\" (IDs 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11)\n3. BUT the `last_icloud_id.txt` should have been `11` - the problem is it wasn't being updated correctly between runs\n\nLooking at the session more carefully, I can see in that session from 11:10 AM:```json{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"11\"}\n```\n\nThat was the last_icloud_id being read as \"11\". So that's correct from the 11:09 AM run. But then the 12:10 PM session also showed \"11\" and still reported all emails... \n\nWait, but the cron job at 12:10 PM read `last_icloud_id` and got \"11\". So it should only report emails with ID > 11. But there were no emails with ID > 11 (the newest is 11). So it should have said \"No new iCloud emails.\"\n\nUnless... the last_icloud_id.txt actually got updated AFTER the email check in the previous run, and that was the FIRST run where it worked correctly (the 11:09 AM run). Then the 12:10 PM run should have worked correctly too.\n\nWait, let me look at the 12:10 PM session to see what last_icloud_id was read as then...\n\nActually, let me just look at what the current session (12:10 PM) reported vs what it should have. The issue is Bobby is seeing the same emails being reported. The last_icloud_id.txt is \"11\" - so if it's being read correctly, no new emails should be reported since the newest is also 11.\n\nBut Bobby is seeing 6 emails reported. \n\nThe last_icloud_id.txt file contains \"11\", yet somehow all 6 emails are still showing up as new. The cron job at 12:10 PM should have read that value and recognized there were no new emails to report, but instead it reported the same ones again. Something's off with how the checkpoint is being read or updated between runs.\n","thinkingSignature":"1d5afc59f107a9a75be896c23758168bf17a30be75b96d5e8efc7fe158942aa1"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nFound the bug. Let me trace it precisely.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ba03tu8da8bz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -200 ~/.openclaw/agents/emmy/sessions/fb7f6b6b-bca0-454a-998b-d19a672336d1.jsonl | strings | grep -E \"last_icloud_id|checkpoint|ID >|ID ≥\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11908,"output":591,"cacheRead":44992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57491,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777479497323,"responseId":"06416249983fe57d54c03a4598b9fc7e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"018548bf","parentId":"2206f9a6","timestamp":"2026-04-29T16:18:32.161Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ba03tu8da8bz_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No new emails'\\n\\n=== MESSAGE 2: ICLOUD (with deduplication) ===\\nSTEP 4 - Read last seen ID: cat ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_id.txt 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"0\\\"\\n\\nSTEP 5 - List iCloud emails (newest first): himalaya envelope list --account icloud 'order by date desc' 2>&1 | grep -v WARN\\n\\nSTEP 6 - For each email where ID > last_seen_ID:\\n  - Read it: himalaya message read <id> --account icloud\\n  - Note its content for reporting\\n\\nSTEP 7 - Send SECOND message to 8212808444 with format:\\n\n No new emails'\\n\\nSTEP 8 - After sending, update checkpoint: echo <highest_new_id> > ~/.openclaw/workspace-emmy/last_icloud_id.txt\\n\\nRULES:\\n- Send the Gmail message FIRST, then the iCloud message immediately after\\n- Only include sections that have emails (skip empty categories)\\n- Keep summaries to 1 line\\n- Mark action needed with \n\\n- ICLOUD: Only report emails with ID strictly greater than the saved last_icloud_id\\nCurrent time: Wednesday, April 29th, 2026 - 12:09 PM (America/New_York) / 2026-04-29 16:09 UTC\\n\\nUse the message tool if you need to notify the user directly for the current chat. If you do not send directly, your final plain-text reply will be delivered automatically.\"}],\"timestamp\":1777478990652}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"cd7b8d7b\",\"parentId\":\"7aa6685a\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-29T16:09:55.921Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me follow the cron job instructions. I need to:\\n1. Check Gmail first using gog\\n2. Send Gmail results as Message 1\\n3. Check iCloud using himalaya with deduplication\\n4. Send iCloud results as Message 2\\n\\nLet me start by running the Gmail check and iCloud envelope list in parallel.\",\"thinkingSignat