{"type":"message","id":"a055b27c","parentId":"db11c341","timestamp":"2026-04-29T23:05:33.317Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The token refresh works with Python but gog fails. This suggests gog might be storing its own separate token that needs to be updated. Since the skill says `gog auth credentials` sets up the credentials, maybe I can use Python's refresh to update the gog token store, or I can try re-authing gog.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach - use the Python Gmail API directly (which works with our refreshed token) to run the email check, rather than relying on gog. I can write a quick script that does the same thing.\n\nOr another option: since my Python script successfully refreshes the token and saves it to credentials_full.json, maybe I can figure out where gog stores its tokens and update them too.\n \nThe issue is that gog might be using a different token store than the credentials file I've been updating. Let me try re-authing gog with the credentials file to see if that gets things working, though I need to be careful about starting the auth server. The Python API approach might be cleaner - I could modify the smart_email_check.py script to use the refreshed token directly instead of relying on gog's separate authentication.\n","thinkingSignature":"3f7c6c2de77ec19c30d3e0ff6772d41311859002659648a676f48bffacbc2aea"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe Python token refresh works fine, but gog has its own separate token store. Let me write a quick test using the Python API to confirm Gmail works, then update the email script to use that instead of gog:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_olcbwer1c044_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nfrom google.oauth2.credentials import Credentials\nfrom googleapiclient.discovery import build\n\ncreds_data = json.load(open('/Users/bobbygalletta/.config/gmail_oauth/credentials_full.json'))\ncreds = Credentials(\n    token=creds_data.get('token'),\n    refresh_token=creds_data.get('refresh_token'),\n    client_id=creds_data.get('client_id'),\n    client_secret=creds_data.get('client_secret'),\n    token_uri='https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token',\n    scopes=['https://mail.google.com/']\n)\ncreds.refresh(__import__('google.auth.transport.requests').Request())\ncreds_data['token'] = creds.token\njson.dump(creds_data, open('/Users/bobbygalletta/.config/gmail_oauth/credentials_full.json', 'w'), indent=2)\n\nservice = build('gmail', 'v1', credentials=creds)\nresults = service.users().messages().list(userId='me', maxResults=5, q='in:inbox newer_than:1h').execute()\nmsgs = results.get('messages', [])\nprint(f\"Found {len(msgs)} recent emails\")\nfor m in msgs:\n    msg = service.users().messages().get(userId='me', id=m['id'], format='metadata', metadataHeaders=['From','Subject','Date']).execute()\n    h = {x['name']: x['value'] for x in msg['payload']['headers']}\n    print(f\"  {h.get('From','')[:40]} | {h.get('Subject','')[:50]}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":210,"output":662,"cacheRead":71616,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72488,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777503916026,"responseId":"0641c1ac6353415627e47ebaf9944fc8"}}
