{"type":"message","id":"127611a4","parentId":"246b8e53","timestamp":"2026-04-29T23:06:09.298Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So gog stores its tokens in the keyring, not in a JSON file. The keyring is probably the macOS keychain. That's why gog still fails - it's using old tokens from the keyring.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The Python script I ran works fine - it uses the credentials_full.json file and successfully refreshes and reads Gmail. So the Gmail integration itself is working.\n\nThe issue is that gog (which is used by the hourly email cron job) has its own token storage (keyring/macOS keychain) and it's expired.\n\nSince my Python script works, maybe I should:\n1. Update the hourly email check script to use the Python approach instead of gog\n\n\n2. Or try to refresh gog's tokens through the browser flow again\n\nActually, let me first try to just re-authenticate gog by running through the browser flow to get a fresh auth code and exchange it for new tokens, then update the keyring.\n","thinkingSignature":"16312f3de9e8b704048775cdd0f2f4c8ad5000972ed587086a36db9bc72970bc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8mfhvl087we0_1","name":"browser","arguments":{"action":"navigate","targetId":"94B309987A1E0DBFAD8AB16C61DF6476","url":"https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/v2/auth?client_id=1038884317442-c84cvhcau9j76o8ej19jtnmig1lbc43s.apps.googleusercontent.com&redirect_uri=http://localhost&response_type=code&scope=https://mail.google.com/&access_type=offline&prompt=consent"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":141,"output":339,"cacheRead":72960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73440,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777503962985,"responseId":"0641c1db6909a84f19c8c676ce738fe5"}}
