{"type":"message","id":"e12bda7c","parentId":"e25342f1","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:37:25.127Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Bobby wants me to read the full thread with Amy (RC Leasing) from his iCloud email. Let me fetch all the messages in that thread using himalaya.\n","thinkingSignature":"2418799f9701f64b6ed222193ef07d9ebae66d7a0729ad3cff9280361f828d6a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sno94av27yq4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"for id in 6 7 8 9 10 11; do\n  echo \"===== ID $id =====\"\n  himalaya message read $id --account icloud 2>/dev/null\n  echo \"\"\ndone"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":81330,"output":108,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":81630,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777513037301,"responseId":"0641e54d68976fa543111ccf7344e826"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2cc15d15","parentId":"e12bda7c","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:37:32.603Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_sno94av27yq4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"===== ID 6 =====\nFrom: Taylor Alexander <taylora.hubrealty@gmail.com>\nTo: Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSubject: Re: Apartment Inquiry (Around mid June)\n\nHello!\n\nWe do only hold apartments for 6 weeks, so it is fairly early to discuss\navailability for June as I am not really sure what we would have at that\ntime.\nYou would want to follow up with me about mid April so I can discuss more\naccurate availability with you.\n\nAt this very moment, I only have 2 bedrooms available. This can change\nbefore June, and we will hopefully have some one bedrooms as well.\nOur 2 bedrooms are renting for $2265 and our 1 bedrooms at $1865, both\noptions including heat and hot water.\n\nPlease keep my information and touch base with me as we get closer.\nI'd love to work something out and help you get settled in with our\ncommunity.\n\nFeel free to reach out if you have any other questions or concerns.\nThank you, look forward to hearing from you!\n\nOn Wed, Jan 21, 2026 at 6:13 PM Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com> wrote:\n\n> Hello,\n>\n> I am interested in relocating to the area in June. I will need to\n> determine the exact dates between my current lease and my move from\n> Tennessee. I understand that this is relatively early in the year, but I am\n> currently researching the areas. I am originally from Wappingers, and one\n> of my close friends resides in the community and has only positive things\n> to say about it. I would love to see if there are any available options.\n>\n> Thank you,\n> Robert Galletta\n>\n>\n\n-- \nTaylor Alexander, Leasing Manager\nRidgefield & Dutchess Apartments\n845-454-2290\n\n\n411 Meadow St.\nFairfield, CT 06824\n203-334-0181\n\nVisit our website\nwww.hubrealty.com\n\nLike us on Facebook\nRidgefield Apartments\n<https://www.facebook.com/Ridgefieldapartmentspoughkeepsie>\nDutchess Apartments\n<https://www.facebook.com/DutchessApartmentsPoughkeepsie>\n\n\n===== ID 7 =====\nFrom: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nTo: Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\nThank you for your interest in Royal Cove! Offering affordable Apartments located in the Town of Poughkeepsie.\nKindly Note: Availability is subject to change throughout the inquiry process.\n1 Bedroom/ 1 Bath starting at $1825.00\n2 Bedroom/ 1 Bath starting at $2150.00\n3 Bedroom/ 1 Bath starting at $2595.00\n\nOnsite Amenities:\nExterior amenities include a swimming pool, playground areas, picnic & grill areas, dog parks and basketball court. Interior amenities include laundry room on site, fully renovated  units, business center, lounge area and fitness center.\nUtilities:\nHeat ,Hot water, garbage, sewer, landscaping, etc. are included.  Electric, cable and internet are additional and paid for by tenants.\nWhat you need to know before applying!\nPet Friendly! One-time pet fee: $400 per dog & $200 per cat. Monthly Pet Rent is $35 per Dog & $25 per cat. No aggressive breeds (Rottweilers, Pit-Bulls, German Shepherds, Dobermans, Chows, etc.).  At full maturity they cannot weigh more than 50lbs. 2 pet maximum.\nOur leases are for 1 year.\n$20 application fee per adult (non-refundable).  All adults residing in the unit must be screened.  The screening process will consist of a credit check, background check, and mandatory pet screening .  You must provide your full social security number for the screening process.\nTotal household NET income 2.5 times the monthly rent is required.    We look for a credit score of 600 or higher\nRhino Partner- Rhino Policies start as low as $9 per month*, compared to an upfront cash deposit.\nAs required per the lease agreement all new tenants will be enrolled in the Waiver Program at an additional $18 per month. Ask us how this program benefits you!\nSpectrum through the property rep starting at $49.99 a month\nPlease let us know if you have already applied to our sister properties: Royal Ledges Aor Royal Gardens\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAmy Smith\n\nLeasing Agent\n\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\n\nW | royalcoveapts.com<https://shared.outlook.inky.com/link?domain=royalcoveapts.com&t=h.eJx1jUEOwiAURK_SsLalvyjQrrwKhQ82YiGUGhvj3YWNO3cvmTczb7InT6aG3HKOE6UpHMrr8EQV89bp8CCnhtyr4PG1rC6HtY0pREz5aF0Ke6RJe1Rbya4_Jbpapb1AaSSCGJjl1poLH80ZJGih55kPQEGIXgLvGe-AyXEU9Q3r29_RaphirLv3BZeC8PkCt98_GQ.MEUCIQCWTK6waHQ5m4oXXmmk0HWUWuJpREFHCvC4dLlg9W3LSQIgBWmuktwnm5U9QNOCLRJfbL_fBqb8ylv8lngBFhSNwTY>\n\n\n\n[A picture containing text, font, screenshot, graphics  Description automatically generated]\n\n\n\nAmy Smith\n\nLeasing Agent\n\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\n\nW | royalcoveapts.com\n\n\n\n[A picture containing text, font, screenshot, graphics  Description automatically generated]\n\n\n\n________________________________\nFrom: Bobby Galletta <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSent: Monday, April 13, 2026 11:12 AM\nTo: RC Leasing <rcleasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nSubject: Looking for new apartment\n\n Hello, I hope you’re doing well. My partner Logan and I are currently searching for a 1-bedroom apartment and are looking to move in by early June, ideally before June 6. We are relocating from Tenn\n[cid:inky-injection-inliner-03755809cc10337ec572b1f12a6beedf]\nCaution: External (rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com>)\nFirst-Time Sender   Details<removed-link>\n[cid:inky-injection-inliner-97c0836b41e87f6018b00b7d2e96af51]\n  Report This Email<removed-link>\n\n Hello,\n\n\nI hope you’re doing well. My partner Logan and I are currently searching for a 1-bedroom apartment and are looking to move in by early June, ideally before June 6.\n\n\nWe are relocating from Tennessee, and I do plan to come up in person to tour the apartment before moving.\n\n\nWe do have a dog named Finnly who is about 50 lbs, so we would also like to know about your pet policies, including any associated fees or restrictions.\n\n\nAdditionally, could you please provide details on what would be required upfront to secure a unit? Specifically, we’re interested in understanding the security deposit, any application or administrative fees, pet fees, and any other initial costs.\n\n\nCould you also let us know if you currently have any 1-bedroom units available, or if you expect any availability to open up before June 6?\n\n\nLastly, are you currently offering any move-in specials or promotions?\n\n\nThank you for your time, and we look forward to hearing from you.\n\n\nBest regards,\n\nRobert Galletta\n<#part type=image/png filename=\"/Users/bobbygalletta/Downloads/image.png\"><#/part>\n<#part type=image/png filename=\"/Users/bobbygalletta/Downloads/Outlook-A picture .png\"><#/part>\n\n\n===== ID 8 =====\nFrom: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nTo: rtg.bobby@icloud.com <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\nGood Morning,\n\nOnce Logan completes his, I can run the apps. When are you looking to move by so I can make sure I will have one Available?\n\n\nAmy Smith\n\nLeasing Agent\n\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\n\nW | royalcoveapts.com\n\n\n\n[A picture containing text, font, screenshot, graphics  Description automatically generated]\n\n\n\n________________________________\nFrom: rtg.bobby@icloud.com <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSent: Saturday, April 25, 2026 1:49 PM\nTo: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\nHi Amy, I wanted to reach out to let you know that I have completed and submitted my portion of the rental application for Royal Cove. I am currently waiting on my partner, Logan, to finish his part o\nReport This Email<removed-link>\n\n\nHi Amy,\n\n\n\nI wanted to reach out to let you know that I have completed and submitted my portion of the rental application for Royal Cove. I am currently waiting on my partner, Logan, to finish his part of the application on his end.\n\n\n\nWe are still very interested in a 1 bedroom / 1 bathroom unit. Please let me know if you need anything else from me in the meantime, or if there are any updates on availability.\n\n\n\nThank you,\n\nRobert Galletta\n<#part type=image/png filename=\"/Users/bobbygalletta/Downloads/Outlook-A picture .png\"><#/part>\n\n\n===== ID 9 =====\nFrom: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nTo: rtg.bobby@icloud.com <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\nHello,\n\nOk sounds good. I may have one for that time frame. Just keep in mind they are first come first serve. Once approved, your application stays with us until we can link you to a unit. Once Logan is done, we can begin the process. Any questions feel free to reach out.\n\n\nAmy Smith\n\nLeasing Agent\n\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\n\nW | royalcoveapts.com\n\n\n\n[A picture containing text, font, screenshot, graphics  Description automatically generated]\n\n\n\n________________________________\nFrom: rtg.bobby@icloud.com <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSent: Monday, April 27, 2026 12:17 PM\nTo: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\nGood afternoon, We were hoping sometime before June 4th. I will follow up once Logan completes his portion of the application. Thank you, Robert Galletta                                              \nReport This Email<removed-link>\n\nGood afternoon,\n\nWe were hoping sometime before June 4th.\nI will follow up once Logan completes his portion of the application.\n\nThank you,\nRobert Galletta\n\n\nOn Apr 27, 2026, at 8:20 AM, RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>> wrote:\n\n\nGood Morning,\n\nOnce Logan completes his, I can run the apps. When are you looking to move by so I can make sure I will have one Available?\n\n\nAmy Smith\n\nLeasing Agent\n\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\n\nW | royalcoveapts.com<https://shared.outlook.inky.com/link?domain=royalcoveapts.com&t=h.eJxNjkEOwiAURK_SsLalQAXbVa8Cnx9sRD-h1NgY764sNG7nzeTNk205sqlh51LSxHmm3UagO9pU1g7oyg4Nu9RCxMdyC4VubcqUMJe9DZm2xDNEtOuHzb9KCnXKHYAAiSNqZ3EEpb0dBiHtUSqPPUoujDGq19qMXX8SRktVdVh1uYTOkXP7vECkzX-_-Ar_otcb3UI-gg.MEUCIQCrAoq9O9zx8X-WiCWAUINSyTP-_NOMlxkZwbLwiSoYkQIgeBorTOa8cgxlkQb1ARuodw22Fxfr2BJ6_Md9GJYWmkA>\n\n\n\n<Outlook-A picture .png>\n\n\n\n________________________________\nFrom: rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com> <rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com>>\nSent: Saturday, April 25, 2026 1:49 PM\nTo: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\n\nHi Amy,\n\n\n\nI wanted to reach out to let you know that I have completed and submitted my portion of the rental application for Royal Cove. I am currently waiting on my partner, Logan, to finish his part of the application on his end.\n\n\n\nWe are still very interested in a 1 bedroom / 1 bathroom unit. Please let me know if you need anything else from me in the meantime, or if there are any updates on availability.\n\n\n\nThank you,\n\nRobert Galletta\n<#part type=image/png filename=\"/Users/bobbygalletta/Downloads/Outlook-A picture .png\"><#/part>\n\n\n===== ID 10 =====\nFrom: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nTo: rtg.bobby@icloud.com <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\nHello,\n\nI wasn't able to see pay stubs, do you both have some you can send me?\n\n\nAmy Smith\n\nLeasing Agent\n\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\n\nW | royalcoveapts.com\n\n\n\n[A picture containing text, font, screenshot, graphics  Description automatically generated]\n\n\n\n________________________________\nFrom: rtg.bobby@icloud.com <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSent: Monday, April 27, 2026 4:02 PM\nTo: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\nHello! Logan and I have both submitted our applications and submitted our documents. Thank you! Robert Galletta                                                                                        \nReport This Email<removed-link>\n\nHello!\n\nLogan and I have both submitted our applications and submitted our documents.\n\nThank you!\nRobert Galletta\n\n\nOn Apr 27, 2026, at 3:06 PM, RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>> wrote:\n\n\nHello,\n\nOk sounds good. I may have one for that time frame. Just keep in mind they are first come first serve. Once approved, your application stays with us until we can link you to a unit. Once Logan is done, we can begin the process. Any questions feel free to reach out.\n\n\nAmy Smith\n\nLeasing Agent\n\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\n\nW | royalcoveapts.com<https://shared.outlook.inky.com/link?domain=royalcoveapts.com&t=h.eJxNjssOgjAURH-FdC2Ulj6AFb_SllqJldtcipEY_1270LidM5MzT7JjJGNFLjmnkVKEw0QHd29S3hoHN3KqyLUUon8sa8iw1gkhecxHHRD2RNFFb7YPm36VFMqUCmWU00PfyfPQGmOtYMI7O3DueqasoUxr3fGWSd5IrgSTXdH5osMcGgvWHtPiIuzz98tc4F_0egOjEz3u.MEQCICsXyG_X4cTZgg-0e9IyTuzVOeNrMT8h6-k7gAqGLetIAiB4rEGZb0mixRUIMYoaWhCZfMtqFLiRhsLl1ogTXk3gFA>\n\n\n\n<Outlook-A picture .png>\n\n\n\n________________________________\nFrom: rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com> <rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com>>\nSent: Monday, April 27, 2026 12:17 PM\nTo: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\nGood afternoon,\n\nWe were hoping sometime before June 4th.\nI will follow up once Logan completes his portion of the application.\n\nThank you,\nRobert Galletta\n\n\nOn Apr 27, 2026, at 8:20 AM, RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>> wrote:\n\n\nGood Morning,\n\nOnce Logan completes his, I can run the apps. When are you looking to move by so I can make sure I will have one Available?\n\n\nAmy Smith\n\nLeasing Agent\n\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\n\nW | royalcoveapts.com<https://shared.outlook.inky.com/link?domain=royalcoveapts.com&t=h.eJxNjssOgjAURH-FdC2Ulj6AFb_SllqJldtcipEY_1270LidM5MzT7JjJGNFLjmnkVKEw0QHd29S3hoHN3KqyLUUon8sa8iw1gkhecxHHRD2RNFFb7YPm36VFMqUCmWU00PfyfPQGmOtYMI7O3DueqasoUxr3fGWSd5IrgSTXdH5osMcGgvWHtPiIuzz98tc4F_0egOjEz3u.MEQCICsXyG_X4cTZgg-0e9IyTuzVOeNrMT8h6-k7gAqGLetIAiB4rEGZb0mixRUIMYoaWhCZfMtqFLiRhsLl1ogTXk3gFA>\n\n\n\n<Outlook-A picture .png>\n\n\n\n________________________________\nFrom: rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com> <rtg.bobby@icloud.com<mailto:rtg.bobby@icloud.com>>\nSent: Saturday, April 25, 2026 1:49 PM\nTo: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\n\nHi Amy,\n\n\n\nI wanted to reach out to let you know that I have completed and submitted my portion of the rental application for Royal Cove. I am currently waiting on my partner, Logan, to finish his part of the application on his end.\n\n\n\nWe are still very interested in a 1 bedroom / 1 bathroom unit. Please let me know if you need anything else from me in the meantime, or if there are any updates on availability.\n\n\n\nThank you,\n\nRobert Galletta\n<#part type=image/png filename=\"/Users/bobbygalletta/Downloads/Outlook-A picture .png\"><#/part>\n\n\n===== ID 11 =====\nFrom: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nTo: rtg.bobby@icloud.com <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\n\nHello,\n\nCan you send me the bank statements you tried to send with the application?\n\n\nAmy Smith\n\nLeasing Agent\n\nT  |  845.452.3450 x312\nE  |  RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com<mailto:RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\n\nW | royalcoveapts.com\n\n\n\n[A picture containing text, font, screenshot, graphics  Description automatically generated]\n\n\n\n________________________________\nFrom: rtg.bobby@icloud.com <rtg.bobby@icloud.com>\nSent: Tuesday, April 28, 2026 9:59 AM\nTo: RC Leasing <RCLeasing@lexingtonpg.com>\nSubject: Re: Looking for new apartment\n\nHello, Yes, we do. We did also send them through the portal along with our IDs and SSN. I will send our pay stubs here as well. There should be two separate files attached, one for Robert, and one for\nReport This Email<removed-link>\n\nHello,\n[... 4446 more characters truncated]"}],"details":{"persistedDetailsTruncated":true,"originalDetailsBytesAtLeast":8193,"originalDetailKeys":["status","exitCode","durationMs","aggregated","cwd"],"status":"completed","cwd":"/Users/bobbygalletta/.openclaw/workspace-emmy","exitCode":0},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777513052599}}
{"type":"message","id":"b2c0f723","parentId":"2cc15d15","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:38:00.730Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full thread. Let me summarize the back-and-forth with Amy (RC Leasing). Bobby is right - it's pretty ridiculous. Let me give him my take on it.\n\nSummary of the thread:\n1. Bobby first reached out to RC Leasing on April 13 asking about the apartment\n2. Amy responded April 13 with pricing info (1BR $1825, 2BR $2150) and details about amenities, pet policy, etc.\n3. Bobby submitted his application portion on April 25, saying Logan still needed to complete his\n4. Amy said \"Ok sounds good. I may have one for that time frame. First come first serve.\"\n5. Bobby confirmed the move-in date hope of before June 4\n\n\n6. Amy then asked if they had pay stubs, even though they had already been submitted through the portal\n7. Bobby pointed out they'd submitted everything - applications, IDs, SSN, and pay stubs - but Amy couldn't see the pay stubs and was asking about bank statements too\n\nIt's the same pattern repeating - Amy keeps asking for documents that were already provided, and when Bobby tries to clarify what was sent and what's missing, the communication gets muddy.\n\nLooking back at the chain, I sent pay stubs and bank statements via email on April 28 after Amy said she couldn't see them, but it seems like some documents are still getting lost in the portal or between email and the application system. I'm now wondering if Logan ever completed his part of the application, since that could be the underlying issue causing all these follow-up requests.\n","thinkingSignature":"17df412a7c54146cf383681c6987bd44354c6b51c3dea01f3f7c9b6f3ce648b6"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nYeah Bobby, you're not wrong. 😅 Here's the full thread:\n\n**Apr 13** — You reach out to RC Leasing about a June move-in. Amy sends pricing ($1825/mo for 1BR) and all the details.\n\n**Apr 25** — You email saying you submitted your part of the application and Logan's still working on his. Amy says \"Ok sounds good, I may have one for that time frame, first come first serve.\"\n\n**Apr 27, 3:06 PM** — Amy suddenly asks \"I wasn't able to see pay stubs, do you both have some you can send me?\"\n\n**Apr 27, 4:02 PM** — You respond \"Logan and I have both submitted our applications and submitted our documents.\"\n\n**Apr 28, 8:40 AM** — Amy AGAIN asks for pay stubs, saying she couldn't see them. Then asks for bank statements too.\n\n**Apr 28, 9:59 AM** — You send the pay stubs via email and say \"There should be two separate files attached, one for Robert and one for Logan. Let me know if you have trouble!\"\n\nAnd then... silence from Amy. She never confirmed she received them or followed up.\n\n---\n\n**Yeah, it's a mess.** Amy can't seem to find documents that are clearly being submitted through the portal AND sent via email. Either their portal is garbage and things get lost, or there's a disconnect between what's in the portal and what she's checking.\n\n**The real question:** Did Amy ever get back to you after you sent those pay stubs on the 28th? Because based on this thread, she went quiet after that — which might mean she finally saw them, or maybe she still hasn't confirmed.\n\nWhat's the status now — did you hear back, or is this stuck?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":6374,"output":695,"cacheRead":81472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":88541,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777513052613,"responseId":"0641e55d35396b125435a33d8d5c24d7"}}
